Cocoa exports from  Ecuador , the
worldâ€™s top grower of flavored beans used in fine chocolate,
rose to 18,272 metric tons in December, an 8 percent increase
from last year, the National Cocoa Exporters Association said.  Shipments increased from 16,918 tons in December 2011,
according to data published today on the website of the
association known as Anecacao.  Ecuador exported 13,997 tons in October and 19,062 tons in
November, while exports in October and November 2011 were 20,761
tons and 27,285 tons, respectively, the data show.  To contact the reporter on this story:
